      I agree with many of your points, Mr. Brenman - I would also add that the EEOC needs to be depoliticized - right now the EEOC seems to be more like the "Fox" guarding the "hen house".  Many of the Judges seem to perpetuate and protect discrimination with their lack of civil rights enforcement. With this sort of body -it's very dangerous for talented individuals to come work for the federal government if there is no recourse for defending one's self and career against unmeritocratic principles and discrimination because of the politicization of the EEOC, and the merit systems protection board.

                  
