      I give a lot of thought to electoral reform issues, of which you have barely scratched the surface, because I believe that if our goal is a society where justice pervades and prevails we will achieve it through the ballot box.  Therefore the systems that make the democratic process work or fail had better be repaired. <br/><br/>That is, ostensibly, why HAVA, the Help America Vote Act was passed 10 years ago. But in fact the Act was a trojan horse designed to promote the adoption of electronic voting machines. <br/><br/>In your long list you make a good suggestion right at the start, "De-politicizing US Commission on Civil Rights: The USCCR has devolved into a mockery of what it was set up to achieve—the study and resolution of social justice issues in the United States."  Having grasped the nature of the politicization of HAVA, it concerns me to think that the USCCR is also a vicitm of connivance.<br/> 

                  
    </td>
